<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by Women’s Aid</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Women’s Aid </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="OLE_LINK3"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women's Aid is the national domestic violence charity that co-ordinates and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supports an England-wide network of over 300 local services working to end domestic violence against women and children.</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Keeping the voices of survivors at the heart of its work, Women's Aid campaigns for better legal protection and services, providing a s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">trategic "expert view" to government on laws, policy and practice affecting abused women and children. In partnership with its national network, Women's Aid runs public awareness and education campaigns, bringing together national and local action, and dev</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">eloping new training and resources.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Women's Aid provides a package of vital 24 hour lifeline services through its publications (available in 11 languages including English</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> and running the Freephone 24 Hour National Domestic Violence Helpline in partne</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">rship with Refuge - 0808 2000 247.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid welcomes the opportunity to submit written evidence to the Work and Pensions Select Committee Inquiry into support for housing costs in the reformed welfare system and will restrict comments to our areas of e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">xpertise. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This response focuses on the implications of changes for survivors of domestic violence and the t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rea</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tment of housing costs within Universal Credit. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Women’s Aid Written Evidence</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid has significant concerns about the impact of changes to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Housing Benefit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and the introduction of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">niversal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">redit on the provision of refuge accommodation and the accessibility of safe accommodation for women and children experiencing domestic v</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">iolence. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As Women’s Aid highlighted in our written submission to the Committee’s Inquiry on Universal Credit in August 2012 our key concern</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> wa</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s that unless supported housing costs are dealt with outside Universal Credit, refuge accommodation services could face drastic cuts in their rental income and will be forced to close. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Any refuge service being forced to close </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">would impact greatly on wome</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n survivors’ ability to access safe accommodation allowing t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hem to escape domestic violence. Women’s Aid most recent survey of our members services found that in 10,981 women and their children were initially unable to access refuge accommodation because t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">here was not enough space. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> welcomed the announcement by Ministers to the committee in September 2012 that ‘exempt accommodation’ would be dealt with outside of Universal Credit and part of a localised system in the longer term. Exempt accommodation is defined in the Universal Credi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t regulations as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">: </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">b) accommodation provided to a claimant by any of the following bodies, where the body providing the accommodation, or a person acting on its behalf, also provides the claimant with care, support or supervision—</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 135pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">(i)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">an upper-tier county coun</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">cil,</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 135pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">(ii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">a housing association,</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 135pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">(iii)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">a registered charity, or</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 135pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">(iv)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">a voluntary organisation.’</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This means that the definition only applies if the support is provided on behalf of the landlord; but current </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">commissioning </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">practice is that in many cases, support is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">commissi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oned on behalf of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">local authority</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, not on behalf of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">landlord</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Women’s Aid’s concerns are that some refuge services could fall outside of this definition of exempt accommodation, as man</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">y are managing agents for the landlord and commissioned to provi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">de support by the local authority or other funders. If this definition does not apply, then women who are temporarily resident in a refuge service would have their housing costs met through Universal Credit, and could also be subject to the spare room subs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">idy (also called the ‘bedroom tax’) and the Benefit cap.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">April 2013, Lord Freud, Minister for Welfare Reform, wrote to Women’s Aid stating that the Government intends to protect supported housing such as refuge accommodation from Universal Credit changes and will be developing solutions to this. The future of Ho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">using Benefit for refuge services therefore still being reviewed by the Department for Work and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Pensions. Women’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Aid hopes that a solution can be found that will allow refuge services to continue to be financially viable. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Women’s Aid believes that there are three key areas of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reform</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that will impact on women experiencing domestic violence and their ability to access safe refuge accommodation. They are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">: </span></li><ol type="a" style