y:Arial; font-size:11pt">as monthly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> payment and assessment. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The spare room subsidy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> may apply to survivors of domestic violence in their own homes, or may apply to refuge services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which are delivered from self-contained accommodation where these are not classed as ‘exempt ac</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">commodation’. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In both circumstances there may be good reasons why the property is ‘under occupied’. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Survivors may be living in property that is suitable because they have increased safety measures in place or because it is located near to key facilities s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">uch as schools. Women’s Aid has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">evidence </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the spare room subsidy being applied to homes where a sanctuary scheme is in place. Sanctuary schemes are intended to enable women to be safe without having to leave their home and therefore becoming homeless. Women’s Aid believes that survivors </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">affected </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">by the spare room subsidy should not be advised to take a lodger or to move to a smaller property if they are settled in appropriate housing in the community. Safer alternatives should be sought with the survivor. Alternatives to eviction for non-payment o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">f rent should be sought where the bedroom tax has reduced housing benefit.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Julia</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">, a survivor of domestic violence who suffered rape, physical assault and harassment at the hands of her partner. Currently, Julia and her 10 year old son, live in a three</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> bedroom house that has been specifically adapted to enable them to live safely in light of the risk posed by Julia’s abuser. A ‘sanctuary system’ has been installed in their home which includes reinforced doors and windows, alarms and a room which Julia c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">an go to safely with a hotline direct to the local police. These measures are necessary to enable Julia and her son to live safely in their home. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Under the Bedroom Tax rules, Julia is only entitled to receive housing benefit for a two bedroom house for her</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">self and her son. She either has to pay the extra rent and go without other essentials, or move to a smaller property. If she can’t pay the extra rent she faces eviction. With very few two-bedroom council houses available, and none with the safety features</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> Julia and her son need, she faces a grave risk from the abuser who has threatened to kill both of them</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0